==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''undulatio''

===Noun===
'''undulation'''
#an instance or act of [[undulate|undulating]]
#a [[wavy]] appearance or outline; [[waviness]]
#''(musical)'' a [[tremulous]] tone produced by a peculiar pressure of the finger on a string
#a [[wavelike]] curve; a smooth and regular rise and fall
#a wavelike motion of the air; electromagnetic radiation

